theatrical /θɪˈætrɪkəl/

1. ADJ Theatrical means relating to the theatre. 戏剧的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...the most outstanding theatrical performances of the year. …年度最杰出的戏剧表演。 

2. theatrically ADV 在戏剧上 

例： Shaffer's great gift lies in his ability to animate ideas theatrically. 谢弗的天赋在于他能把想法在戏剧上表现出来。 

3. ADJ Theatrical behaviour is exaggerated and unnatural, and intended to create an effect. (行为) 夸张的 

例： In a theatrical gesture Jim clamped his hand over his eyes. 以一个夸张的手势，吉姆用一只手紧紧捂住双眼。 

4. theatrically ADV 夸张地 

例： He looked theatrically at his watch. 他夸张地看了看表。

</div>

